        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6987286-john-alee?shelf=cookbooks">cookbooks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6987286-john-alee?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6987286-john-alee?shelf=pop-sugar-2020">pop-sugar-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6987286-john-alee?shelf=2020-goodreads-reading-challenge">2020-goodreads-reading-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6987286-john-alee?shelf=my-joy-project">my-joy-project</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6987286-john-alee?shelf=books-bought-in-2020">books-bought-in-2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3278170858" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9441831330946858739">Wow... Wow.... Wow!! I wish I could give this little book 100 stars! <br/><br/>I love to cook and create in the kitchen and have been doing so for almost 40 years. I’ve read cookbooks like most people read novels for just as long yet I have never come across a book about cooking that has resonated deep within my soul, and has changed my way of thinking about food and how to prepare it! The essence of this book is learning how to take what you have and not only to make a meal of it, but to also use the lef</span>
  <span id="freeText9441831330946858739" style="display:none">Wow... Wow.... Wow!! I wish I could give this little book 100 stars! <br /><br />I love to cook and create in the kitchen and have been doing so for almost 40 years. I’ve read cookbooks like most people read novels for just as long yet I have never come across a book about cooking that has resonated deep within my soul, and has changed my way of thinking about food and how to prepare it! The essence of this book is learning how to take what you have and not only to make a meal of it, but to also use the leftovers of it, the ends of it to start another meal. Pasta waters, juice from a pot of beans, burned onions, over salted rice and the list goes on and on. When you read the book you feel as if you’ve pulled up a chair in a friend’s kitchen and you’re having a conversation with one who understands what ‘the heart of the home ’ is, and they’re sharing their deepest secrets with you. I can’t recommend this little gem enough!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="9441831330946858739" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
